The past few months have been exhausting and exhilarating at the same time because I’ve been shooting non-stop! And, in the entire journey, Carmesi has helped me so much in making things easier. This brand has stolen my heart with the wonderful job they’re doing at creating safe, gentle, and natural products for every woman out there! As many of you are aware, I joined hands with Carmesi earlier this year and, as a result, I’ve tried out all their products. But two of them have genuinely become my staples now!

I’ve always had issues with pad rashes. Couple that with the insane amount of time I spend shooting (and sweating), the rashes would just keep getting worse. But, their Sensitive Sanitary Pads have been a game-changer for me. They just made the rashes go poof! I mean, I’ve never been this comfortable on my period before! And the fact that they come with disposal bags just makes it so much easier for me to discard them while I’m traveling or shooting!

There’s another product that I’ve enjoyed using on the go just as much as the pads. I talk about it in the video and you should watch it to find out! Oh, and did I mention that they have a Flat 25% OFF on these products? Just visit www.mycarmesi.com to get your hands on them. I’m sure you’ll love them as much as I do!

#rashfreepads #periods #menstruation #bodyrazor #bodyhair #hairremoval #MyCarmesi #CarmesiPads

Even as the world slowly challenges the stigma attached to menstruation, a crucial aspect remains unchanged. We still associate women and girls with menstruation - starting from the way we speak about it to the way period products are marketed only keeping women in mind. In doing so, we leave out a community that also bleeds but does not identify as women - trans men.

As a result, they feel shame about their menstruating bodies while battling with society - always scared of being bullied or beaten. They are also frightened to speak up about the emotional trauma that they face regarding their gender identity. 

This Menstrual Hygiene Day, @mycarmesi, in partnership with @anuragchauhanofficial, Founder - Humans for Humanity, is shedding light on the plight of these menstruating trans men and why introducing gender-neutral toilets is the need of the hour - because everyone deserves access to safe menstrual hygiene management!

I urge you to share this video as much as possible, using #HumansWhoPeriod. Further, you can opt to volunteer with Humans for Humanity under their WASH project to help spread awareness about menstrual health and hygiene. 

#HumansWhoPeriod #MyCarmesi #CarmesiPads  #MenstrualHygieneDay2022 #MenstrualHygieneDay #MenstrualHygiene

I would be lying if I told you that I warmed up to menstrual cups instantly. In fact, I was really scared at the thought of trying one. I had all sorts of fears circling in my head. What if it hurts? What if it doesn’t go in? What if it gets lost?

But, all my fears were put to rest when I actually used the Carmesi Menstrual Cup. It’s so soft and comfortable that I honestly didn’t feel a thing. I literally forgot that I was on my period! Yes, it’s that comfortable! And, to top it off, I didn’t experience a single instance of leaks! How cool is that?

If you asked me to rate the best feeling in this world, it would probably be not feeling your period even when you’re actually menstruating! Is there anything that can top this? Probably not!

#MenstrualCups #MyCarmesi

This heat wave has been exhausting to live with, even with access to ACs, fans, and a home to live in. Then my thoughts went to the stray pooches on our streets that don't even have food and water, let alone a roof over their heads to protect them from the harsh sun. 

Luckily, @plumgoodness recently started a wonderful new initiative to get their tails wagging in joy and comfort. Through their #Empties4Good campaign, they're taking back empties of all Plum products and recycling them to be used as insulation in dog shelters all across Mumbai, soon coming to neighbourhoods across Mumbai and Thane.

I'm glad to be associated with a brand that truly spreads the goodness they talk about, especially to those without a voice to ask for help 💜
